From 863adb5cc1c690e87dec86adf0cc836d5cc5ee4d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: regksem <regksem@tuta.io>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 21:36:11 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Add MOTD ping caching, /xwaterfall reload, configurable
 event-loop threads (patch 0075)

Cache the rendered custom-MOTD component for a configurable window
(motd.cache-ttl, default 30s) so the MiniMessage/legacy parse no longer runs
on every server-list ping; the live player count stays fresh per ping. Add a
/xwaterfall motd reload command to re-read the motd.* section of xwaterfall.yml
and clear the cache on demand.

Also make the Netty boss/worker event-loop thread counts configurable
(network.boss-threads default 1, network.worker-threads default 0=auto); the
groups are now created after config load. The boss group only accepts
connections, so a single thread avoids wasting idle threads.

